The paper is about a new model of membership query learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper discusses the learnability of various classes of functions under this new model, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and complexity theory, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
